You know, it's not because that there is DRU on an item that it means that a druid MUST wear it, I can't see any benefit for a sane druid to prefer a CoT over CoS ...<br>
<br>
12 str ! yay I can wear more items ... wait I can buff my str<br>
12 sta ! yay that's 25hp for a druid ... woopie<br>
10dr/pr ... *cough* no comment ... as a druid I'm taking so often poison or disease AEs that I keep them under 100 ... /sarcasm off<br>
10ac ... *laugh* there are enough items in game that will lead a druid to 1000ac ... what's the point of having an ac over 1000 for a druid ? ... answer : NONE !!!<br>
<br>
If you're able to think that the cloak of thorns is better than the cloak of sky only because of these futile stats, you're wrong. I would really feel bad if I had gotten a CoT over any warrior. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unuviancaelestis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nuvian Caelestis</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.rpgicons.com/images/icons/ff6/bosses/hidonite.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/6/02 4:19:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26292.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.rpgicons.com/images/icons/ff7/faces/caitsith.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Weeeee.</span><hr size=1> 12sta = 36hps. 15agi is how much ac for us? I forget the formula, I would assume like 6 or 7, so CoT isn't actually 10ac more.<br>
