</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ustormhaven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stormhaven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>FAQ/Index Moderator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/9/02 2:40:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26292.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://web2.airmail.net/naomi/amalgam/forum/stormhaven.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> CoT</span><hr size=1> The CoT had been high on my list of things to get for a while now... unfortunately it seems to be the rarest #)$* drop.  I agree that this is a warrior cloak first, however when it comes between rangers and druids I think it's a toss up.<br>
<br>
If you have a chance at looting this cloak, I think it's pretty safe to assume you're in a pretty good guild where the primary concern is high-level raids.  <br>
<br>
Here are the two cloaks being suggested, side-by-side:<br>
===<br>
Cloak of Thorns  +35 AC +12 Str +12 Sta +12 Dex +15 Wis +10 vsPos +10 vsDis +100 HP +50 Mana <br>
====<br>
Cloak of the Sky AC: +25 Agi: +15 Wis: +15 HP: +100 Mana: +100 <br>
 <br>
Lets throw WIS right out the window.  If you're raiding NToV chances are you're already at 255 WIS or near enough that you're not too concerned about it.  <br>
<br>
That leaves you with AC, HP and Mana to consider.  The CotS wins with the 100/100 combo, however the CoT catches up by offering 10 more AC and the other secondary stats - leaving both cloak about equal.  So once again it comes back to the same old &quot;what kind of druid are you&quot; question.  <br>
<br>
AC and HP is becoming more and more of a concern to raiding druids as Luclin mobs seem to love taking pot shots at every player in the general vicinity.  Also, early healing by druids can sometimes get us on the rampage list.  It's becoming more and more critical that the druid be able to survive a flurry level attack at least twice, if not three times.  (Yes, I know in an ideal situation that the druid won't get hit at all, but not every raid is picture perfect).<br>
<br>
I'm also very big &quot;pro-resist,&quot; so the 10 svp/svd on the CoT nets a few extra brownie points with me.  Svp/svd are usually my lowest base resists, and a little extra never hurts.<br>
<br>
So when I look at CoT vs CotS, the only thing that appeals to me about the Cloak of the Sky is the additional 50 mana... but all in all, the Cloak of Thorns easily wins over in the big picture. <p><body link="#FFFFFF" vlink="#CCCCCC">

